				</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">As a customer, the prices look great.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
To tell the truth Walmart prices arent that much cheaper than many other (chain) stores for the same items.  In some cases you might pay more for particular items at a Wal Mart than you would at a local grocery store.
<br />
The big selling point of Walmart is and will always be getting everything in one convienent stop.  No longer do you have to go to 3 or 4 stores to get all your staurday shopping done, and that is the brillance of model.
<br />
Heck many stores are trying to copy the walmart model, notice that grocery stores started carrying dvds, clothes etc now?
<br />

<br />
Wal Mart definately can kill small businesses as a small family owned store really can not compete with the mega power of the Wal Mart corperation.  Is this wrong or simply a change in how business should thrive in the free market based system we have set up?  You could go either way on the issue.
<br />
However highly specialized (and expensive) stores will be unaffected due to the fact Wal Mart really can't break into that market.<br />
