				<div class="postbody">
				I asaw wal-mart kill a small town where I went to school.  That, however is not the only reason my household is not allowed to shop there.
<br />

<br />
There are many reasons.  One of the biggest is the sign on the front door that proudly proclaims "we drug test our employees".  Why would I care if the guy putting tampons on the self smokes pot or not?  What I do care about is that Wal-Mart thinks that it should be in a position to scrutenize the most private aspects of a persons life to work for them.
<br />

<br />
The wage they pay their wmployees is disgusting.  This is furthur evidence of the monsterous inhuman machine Wal-Mart is.  If they treat their assets with such horrific disrespect, how do you think they are going to treat your community?
<br />

<br />
The wall of missing children at the entrance of every Wal-Mart turns my stomach.  I know the world is a place where unspeakable horrors happen.  I cannot bring myself to want to walk into a place of business that thinks it is socially responsible to ingrain the rare and disgusting as prevalent and applauded.  I have a running joke going that attributes each of those pictures as children eaten by Wal-Mart managers and claim it is a trophy display.
<br />

<br />
When you spend money close to home, it has a MUCH better chance of coming back to you.  Wal-Mart is the ultimate evil when it comes to draining the economy of anyplace that has one.  The money goes in, it NEVER comes out.
<br />

<br />
There is so much about Wal-Mart that turns me off at a basic level, I openly chastise people that shop there.  I encourage all like minded people to do the same.<br />
